- "gold members" refers to customers with a gold membership status;
- "average fare" refers to the average total price of bookings.

- 'Confirmed' bookings are those that have been successfully processed and are not pending or cancelled;
- 'Total revenue' is the sum of the total prices of all confirmed bookings for a specific route;
- 'Membership status' of the highest spender is determined by the total price of their bookings;
- 'Recent' bookings are those with the latest booking dates;
- 'Highest-priced' bookings are those with the highest total prices.

sql:
SELECT customer_id, total_price
FROM bookings
WHERE total_price > (SELECT AVG(total_price) FROM bookings);

external_knowledge:
- 'Above-average route revenue' means the total revenue for the route is higher than the average revenue across all routes;
- 'Long lead times' refers to an average purchase lead time greater than 30 days;
- 'High flight ratings' indicates a rating greater than 4;
- 'Default vegetarian meal preference' means the customer has a default meal option set to 'vegetarian'.

sql:
SELECT booking_id, status
FROM booking_history
ORDER BY status_change_date DESC;

